issue.title: [CF 313] Assertion Failure with last Alpha Build on 4.3 PTR
issue.body:
Everytime I try to cache the spell names, when it finishes I get an assertion error and WoW closes down.

Tried this in two locales: enUS, ptBR.

Race/Class: Blood Elf Warrior - Level 85 Premade - Arms Spec


> Posted by CurseForge user phalk | Imported from CurseForge issue #313 | Raw

comments.body:
Clicking "Finish Cache Now" also gives the same error. I don't know if it's related to the previous error that was fixed in an earlier release or not.


> Posted by CurseForge user phalk

You need to post the error.


> Posted by CurseForge user Cybeloras

Ah, yeah, here it is, sorry:
I'm not sure if it's a failure related to the addon or a general crash caused by PTR failure, but it's triggered by the addon.
Other addons were also causing this, so I guess it's part on blizzard's fault, because I think addons shouldn't be able to crash WoW like this.
